Package com.adobe.livecycle.rightsmanagement.client.infomodel

Provides classes and interfaces for creating and manipulating objects that represent Document Security collateral, such as licenses, policies, and watermarks.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
AbstractPolicy The AbstractPolicy interface provides methods for creating and manipulating abstract policies.
AbstractPolicyEntry The AbstractPolicyEntry interface defines the set of permissions to provide in the Abstract policy.
Event The Event interface provides methods for retrieving information about Right Management service events.
License The License interface provides methods for retrieving information about licenses and the XML representation of licenses.
Permission The Permission interface defines the constants that represent the different types of policy permissions.
Policy The Policy interface provides methods for creating and manipulating policies.
PolicyEntry The PolicyEntry interface defines the set of permissions to provide a specified principal.
PolicySet The PolicySet interface provides methods for creating and manipulating policy sets.
ValidityPeriod The ValidityPeriod interface provides methods for defining a period of time that a policy provides principals with access to the documents that it protects.
Watermark The Watermark interface defines methods for the creation and manipulation of watermarks.
Watermark2 The Watermark2 interface defines methods for the creation and manipulation of watermarks.
 

Class Summary
AbstractPolicySearchFilter The AbstractPolicySearchFilter class is used to specify search criteria when searching for abstract policies.
EventSearchFilter Enables you to define search criteria that are used while searching for events.
InfomodelObjectFactory The InfomodelObjectFactory class provides methods for creating new objects that are used with Rights Management service.
LicenseSearchFilter The LicenseSearchFilter class is used to specify search criteria when searching for licenses.
PolicySearchFilter The PolicySearchFilter class is used to specify search criteria when searching for policies.
PolicySetCoordinatorAndPerms The PolicySetCoordinatorAndPerms interface provides methods for creating and manipulating policy set co-ordinators and their permissions.
Watermark2Element The Watermark2Element interface defines methods for the creation and manipulation of watermark elements.
 

Exception Summary
PDRLException The PDRLException class defines the exception thrown when an XML document with invalid XML is used as a method paramter.
 

Package com.adobe.livecycle.rightsmanagement.client.infomodel Description

Provides classes and interfaces for creating and manipulating objects that represent Document Security collateral, such as licenses, policies, and watermarks.
